<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<!-- Guard start -->
<FTL>
<textList name="TEXT_START_RADIKAL">
	<text>You have arrived in the RadiKal sector, where specialists from everywhere come in search of highly efficient and illegal gear.
		
		While individual rebels or small groups certainly work with the RadiKals, the fleet will have trouble getting here, giving you some time to prepare for getting out of here alive.
		And prepare you should.
	</text>
	<text>You have arrived in the RadiKal sector, where one can find hazardous equipment of great power, if they're ready to make sacrifices.
		
		While individual rebels or small groups certainly work with the RadiKals, the fleet will have trouble getting here, giving you some time to prepare for getting out of here alive.
		And prepare you should.
	</text>
	<text>You have arrived in the RadiKal sector, which should be fine if you know what you're looking for, and when to avoid fights you might not win.
		
		While individual rebels or small groups certainly work with the RadiKals, the fleet will have trouble getting here, giving you some time to prepare for getting out of here alive.
		And prepare you should.
	</text>
</textList>

<!-- Called by sector_data -->
<event name="START_RADIKAL">
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_start" global="false">
		<color r="46" g="252" b="51" a="1"/>
	</beaconType>
	<text load="TEXT_START_RADIKAL"/>
	<modifyPursuit amount="-2"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_GUARD_RADIKAL" hostile="false"/>

	<changeBackground>BACK_SECTOR_CIVILIAN</changeBackground>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="GUARD_RADIKAL"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<!-- . -->
<event name="GUARD_RADIKAL">
	<text>The beacon is guarded by a well armed vessel but it's not hostile just yet. In the distance you see pirate ship jumping away. From what you can tell, they're loaded with cargo and the guard just let them through, with no recent signs of battle.
		
		The guard is hailing you.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Respond to the hail.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Hey there. Rook or reg?" The guard is nonchalantly awaiting your answer.
				This seems to be about your familiarity with this sector.
			</text>

			<choice req="DJMOD_HAS_RADIKAL_GEAR" hidden="true">
				<text>(Any piece of RK gear) Reg. Hit me up!</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Nice piece! Since you're already one of us, here are all the latest coordinates, in case you want to diversify your options." With that, the guard is already busy with the next ship.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Here's the current location of the RadiKal Bam lab, if you have explodey stuff, or need more, you know they'll be happy to see you."</text>
							<quest event="RKS_QUEST_LAB_BAM">
								<!-- <nextSector>false</nextSector>
								<aggressive>2</aggressive> -->
							</quest>
							<variable name="rks_lab_coords_bam" op="set" val="1"/>
							
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Sly as always, the Punk have set camp at this beacon. For all your fancy needs."</text>
									<quest event="RKS_QUEST_LAB_PUNK">
										<!-- <nextSector>false</nextSector>
										<aggressive>2</aggressive> -->
									</quest>
									<variable name="rks_lab_coords_punk" op="set" val="1"/>
									
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event>
											<text>"... and here's the Scorch lab. They're in need of supplies. You know, the kind that burns really well...
												Safe travels! Hahaha"
												
												If you had to guess, the "supplies" might be living creatures, which could mean all sorts of trouble.
												You'll decide what to do on the way, there's nothing left to do here but some maintenance.
											</text>
											<quest event="RKS_QUEST_LAB_SCORCH">
												<!-- <nextSector>false</nextSector>
												<aggressive>2</aggressive> -->
											</quest>
											<variable name="rks_lab_coords_scorch" op="set" val="1"/>
					
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Check the storage.</text>
												<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
											</choice>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Do nothing.</text>
												<event/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>

			<choice req="DJMOD_HAS_RADIKAL_GEAR" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false">
				<text>You do not have any RadiKal gear. You're not flying an RK ship either.</text>
				<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
			</choice>
	
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Rook.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Yeah no wonder. Your ship looks like it could use serious upgrades. Do you even know what you're looking for in here?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Yes.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Alright, what's it gonna be?." The guard has brought up a short list of destinations on the comms, with only codenames and all the usual details are missing. You are starting to wonder just how shady a place you just found yourself in.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Pick "Bam".</text>
								<event>
									<text>"The classics, always reliable. A wise choice." The guard transmits the coordinates to you, then quickly cuts comms before you can answer.</text>
									<!-- <quest event="QUEST_LANIUS_ZOLTAN_PEACE"/> -->
									<quest event="RKS_QUEST_LAB_BAM">
										<!-- <nextSector>false</nextSector>
										<aggressive>2</aggressive> -->
									</quest>
									<variable name="rks_lab_coords_bam" op="set" val="1"/>
									
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Check the storage.</text>
										<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
									</choice>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Do nothing.</text>
										<event/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Pick "Punk".</text>
								<event>
									<text>"A timely choice, I heard they've got some new stuff available." The guard transmits the coordinates to you, then quickly cuts comms before you can answer.</text>
									<quest event="RKS_QUEST_LAB_PUNK">
										<!-- <nextSector>false</nextSector>
										<aggressive>2</aggressive> -->
									</quest>
									<variable name="rks_lab_coords_punk" op="set" val="1"/>
									
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Check the storage.</text>
										<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
									</choice>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Do nothing.</text>
										<event/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Pick "Scorch".</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Looking for hot stuff, I see." The guard transmits the coordinates to you, then quickly cuts comms before you can answer.</text>
									<quest event="RKS_QUEST_LAB_SCORCH">
										<!-- <nextSector>false</nextSector>
										<aggressive>2</aggressive> -->
									</quest>
									<variable name="rks_lab_coords_scorch" op="set" val="1"/>
									
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Check the storage.</text>
										<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
									</choice>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Do nothing.</text>
										<event/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Not in the least.</text>
						<event>
							<text>The guard frowns. "Not sure how you people got here but this isn't a place for tourists. You better head for the exit without taking any detours, and there won't be trouble." You then hear the guard mutter something about "needing to tighten security again" before comms are cut and you realize that they're already dealing with next arrival.
							
							You move on, confused and slightly worried.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Check the storage.</text>
								<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Do nothing.</text>
								<event/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>This here the pirate haven, innit? We'ere for business. *Spit*</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Oh." The guard seems slightly annoyed, either tired of clearing things up every time or unimpressed by your overdone attitude. "You are slightly mistaken, piracy isn't our focus, unbound progress is more like it. But yes you can conduct what's called illegal types of trade here. I'll let your interests be known to all interested parties, and you... make SURE to bring enough scrap."
						
						They send you the coordinates and let you past. Despite the secrecy of this sector you can already tell that this will reflect poorly on your general reputation.
					</text>

					<!-- The "quest event" parameters are in the event itself, seems to work better overall. -->
					<quest event="RKS_PIRATE_TRINITY"/>

					<variable name="rks_pirate_trinity_active" op="add" val="1"/>
					
					<choice>
						<text>Piracy is kinda poggers. Worth it.</text>
						<event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_PIRATES"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore them and try to fly past.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Their weapons immediately come online, they've clearly been expecting this. This could probably have been avoided by exchanging a few words, but they've already called for backup.
			Surprisingly, it seems that their ship's O2 system has caught fire...</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<environment type="PDS" target="player"/>
			
			<!-- Plasma teleporter effect (the player was warned by the icon) -->
			<playSound>dj_plasmaTeleporter</playSound>
			<enemyDamage amount="0" system="oxygen" effect="fire"/>			
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Hah! What an idio-</text>
				<event>
					<text>Suddenly, you hear strange teleportation sounds in your ship but detect no boarders, just heat signatures... Your ship is also on fire! And quite a bit more than theirs.
					If you survive this, you might just find out how what happened and how to take advantage of it.</text>
					
					<!-- Plasma teleporter effect part 2 -->
					<damage amount="0" system="room" effect="fire"/>
					<damage amount="0" system="room" effect="fire"/>
					<damage amount="0" system="room" effect="fire"/>
					
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>


<ship name="SHIP_GUARD_RADIKAL" auto_blueprint="DJMOD_RADIKAL_GUARD">
	<surrender min="999" max="999" load="GUARD_SIGNAL"/>
	<destroyed load="GUARD_RADIKAL_DESTROY"/>
	<deadCrew load="GUARD_RADIKAL_DEADCREW"/>
	<crew>
		<crewMember type="rock_commando" prop="0.20"/>  
		<crewMember type="phantom_goul" prop="0.20"/>
		<crewMember type="shell" prop="0.20"/>
		<crewMember type="slug_clansman" prop="0.20"/>
		<crewMember type="zoltan_devotee" prop="0.20"/>
	</crew>
</ship>

<event name="GUARD_RADIKAL_DESTROY">
	<text>You have defeated the RadiKal guard. Whatever might have been in their cargo has for certain been destroyed, but you can at least salvage some supplies from the ship.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="GUARD_RADIKAL_FOLLOWUP"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="GUARD_RADIKAL_DEADCREW">
	<text>You have defeated the RadiKal guard. Without crew on-board to stop you, you can investigate their cargo. You find some loot to bring back to the ship, and move on to scrap their hull.</text>
	
	<!-- stuff: Means less scrap more resources -->
	<autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
	
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>You find spare RadiKal equipment!</text>
			<augment name="GIFTLIST_RADIKAL_GUARD"/>	<!-- GIFTLISTS WITH MIXED TYPES DONT WORK, NEVER DID. -->
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="GUARD_RADIKAL_FOLLOWUP"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<ship name="SHIP_RADIKAL_REINFORCEMENTS" auto_blueprint="LIST_SHIPS_RADIKAL_FIGHT">
	<destroyed load="DESTROYED_REINFORCEMENTS"/>
	<deadCrew load="DEADCREW_REINFORCEMENTS"/>
	<crew>
		<crewMember type="rock_commando" prop="0.20"/>  
		<crewMember type="phantom_goul" prop="0.20"/>
		<crewMember type="shell" prop="0.20"/>
		<crewMember type="slug_clansman" prop="0.20"/>
		<crewMember type="zoltan_devotee" prop="0.20"/>
	</crew>
</ship>
<event name="GUARD_RADIKAL_FOLLOWUP">
	<noQuestText/>
	<removeHazards/>
	<clearCustomFleet/>
	<text>By killing the RadiKal guard, you have no doubt caused them to dispatch reinforcements to track you down. Watch your step as you explore the sector.</text>
	<quest event="REINFORCEMENTS_RADIKAL">
		<nebulaBeacon>true</nebulaBeacon>
		<nextSector>false</nextSector>
		<nebulaEvent>NEBULA_REINFORCEMENTS_RADIKAL</nebulaEvent>
		<aggressive>2</aggressive>
	</quest>
	<choice>
		<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
		<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Do nothing.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="REINFORCEMENTS_RADIKAL">
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_reinforcements" global="true" req="LOOT_COMPASS">
		<color r="200" g="55" b="82" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>An unvisited location.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
		<undiscoveredTooltip>An unvisited location.</undiscoveredTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<text>"Someone has to be the guard. They were just doing their job, and knew the risks. But so did you!" The RadiKal ship attacks!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_RADIKAL_REINFORCEMENTS" hostile="true"/>
	<environment type="PDS" target="player"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="NEBULA_REINFORCEMENTS_RADIKAL">
	<preventQuest/>
	<beaconType id="map_icon_reinforcements" global="true" req="LOOT_COMPASS">
		<color r="200" g="55" b="82" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>An unvisited location.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
		<undiscoveredTooltip>An unvisited location.</undiscoveredTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<text>"Someone has to be the guard, they were just doing their job and knew the risks. But so did you!" The RadiKal ship attacks!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_RADIKAL_REINFORCEMENTS" hostile="true"/>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_LIGHTNEBULA"/>
	<status type="loss" target="player" system="sensors" amount="1"/>
	<environment type="PDS" target="player"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>

</FTL>





